data.text:
Fast and Free shipping in the US!

International shipping available: Contact us at support@landogiants.com for a custom quote.

Proprietary blend developed by Joel Holland!

With trace minerals, 9 species of Endomycorrhizal Fungi, 10 beneficial bacteria, seaweed, and humic acid, Kick-A-Poo is the perfect all-inclusive fertilizer for root-drench and foliar application.

BENEFITS:

Every time you feed your plants Kick-A-Poo Joy Juice, you supply the 3 primary nutrients, an important array of minor elements, plus 9 Endomycorrhizal fungi, and 10 beneficial microbes. This combination of Mycorrhizal species and beneficial microbes was created by Doctor Michael Ammaranthus to complement each other and work well together. Dr. Mike is one of the leading authorities in the world on Mycorrhizal Fungi.

DIRECTIONS:

Use 1 tablespoon per gallon when plants are small and progress up to 2 to 3 tablespoons per gallon after the plants are well established. Root drench 1 time per week. After plants are established, foliar feed and/or root drench every 7 to 10 days.

ACTIVE INGREDIENTS:

9 species Endomycorrhizae (1,875 Propagules per pound total):

Glomus intraradices, Glomus mosseae, Glomus aggregatum, Glomus etunicatum, Glomus deserticola, Glomus clarum, Glomus monosporum, Paraglomus brasilianum, Gigaspora margarita.

10 species Ectomycorrhizae (OVER 100,000 Propagules per gram total):

Rhizopogon villosulus, Rhizopogon luteolus, Rhizopogon amylopogon, Rhizopogon fulvigleba, Pisolithus tinctorius, Scleroderma cepa, Scleroderma citrinum, Suillus granulatus, Laccaria bicolor, Laccaria laccata.

Trace Minerals:

Water Soluble Magnesium (.05%), Combined Sulfur (.07%), Boron (.01%), Chelated Copper (.01%), Chelated Iron (.025%), Chelated Manganese (.01%), Molybdenum (.000045%), Chelated Zinc (.01%).
